original: El presidente de la Comisión de Derechos Humanos del Parlasur, Gastón Harispe, sostuvo que en América Latina existe un “achicamiento de la democracia a condiciones mínimas”, a raíz de una “militarización del escenario político”. El martes (22/9), a partir de las 10am, a través del Facebook del Parlasur, el organismo regional desarrollará una audiencia pública por las garantías electorales en Bolivia de la que participarán el Tribunal Supremo Electoral, las bancadas principales de la Asamblea Plurinacional de Bolivia y la Defensoría del Pueblo de Bolivia.
translated: President of the Commission on Human Rights Parlasur Gaston Harispe said that in Latin America there is a "hollowing of democracy to minimum conditions" following a "militarization of the political scene". On Tuesday (22/9), from 10am, through the Facebook of the Parlasur, the regional body held a public hearing by the electoral guarantees in Bolivia of the participation of the Supreme Electoral Tribunal, the major caucuses of the Plurinational Assembly of Bolivia and the Ombudsman of the People of Bolivia.

translated: The president of the Bolivian University Confederation, Max Mendoza, denounced the serious situation facing public universities. "Since April we have been warning, some thought it was scaremongering, but according to how they came running budget projections eleven universities showed us that we would arrive in September with red," he said.

original: Bolivia elegirá a su nuevo gobierno el 18 de octubre. translated: Bolivia elect a new government on 18 October. Therefore "we urge the de facto government of Bolivia to end all political persecution, inescapable condition for the holding of free, transparent and democratic elections." And six national and international human rights organizations in the General Debate of the 45th session of the Human Rights Council of the United Nations Organization (UN) recently spoke in Geneva, Switzerland.

En la provincia de Salta, límite con Bolivia, se estima que serán alrededor de 30 mil personas las que podrán acceder al voto.
translated: Argentina's national government approved the protocol of security measures and health so that Bolivians living in that country can participate in the general elections on October 18. In the province of Salta, bordering Bolivia, it is estimated to be around 30 thousand people who can access the vote.

Personalidades de Canadá y organizaciones internacionales pidieron al gobierno de ese país interceda ante la  Organización de las Naciones Unidas (ONU), la Organización de Estados Americanos (OEA), la Oficina del Alto Comisionado de las Naciones Unidas para los Derechos Humanos (Acnudh) y ante la Comisión Interamericana de Derechos Humanos (CIDH) para que en Bolivia se lleven a cabo elecciones limpias, sin violencia y cuyos resultados sean respetados por la administración transitoria de la presidenta Jeanine Áñez.
translated: People from Canada and international organizations called on the government of that intercedes country to the United Nations (UN), the Organization of American States (OAS), the Office of the High Commissioner of the United Nations for Human Rights (OHCHR) and before the Inter-American Commission on Human Rights (CIDH) in Bolivia to carry out fair elections without violence and whose results are respected by the transitional administration of president Jeanine Áñez.

original: El presidente de la Confederación Nacional de la Micro y Pequeña Empresa (Conamype), Agustín Mamani, aseguró que sólo el 1% de las empresas de su sector accede a los muy promocionados créditos oficiales, porque los requisitos son “inaccesibles” y denuncia que al gobierno sólo le interesa apoyar a las empresas medianas y grandes.
translated: The president of the National Confederation of Micro and Small Enterprises (Conamype), Agustín Mamani said that only 1% of companies in the access sector highly touted government loans, because the requirements are "inaccessible" and denounces that the government is only interested in supporting medium and large enterprises.

La vocera política del Movimiento Al Socialismo (MAS), Marianela Paco, denunció este lunes (12/10) ante la comunidad internacional y el pueblo boliviano que está en curso un segundo golpe a la democracia por la ausencia total de transparencia en el conteo rápido de votos del Tribunal Supremo Electoral (TSE), el retorno de los veedores de la OEA, la declaratoria de toque de queda por seis días y la custodia de las actas por parte de militares y policías que participaron en golpe del año pasado.
translated: Political spokeswoman movement Socialism (MAS), Marianela Paco, denounced on Monday (12/10) to the international community and the Bolivian people that is ongoing a second blow to democracy by the total lack of transparency in counting fast vote of the Supreme Electoral Tribunal (TSE), the return of observers from the OAS, the declaration of a curfew for six days and custody of the records by military and police officers involved in coup last year.

“Las culturas son el alma de nuestro Estado Plurinacional”, dijo Lucho Arce cuando se supo que el gobierno transitorio de Jeanine Áñez suprimió el Ministerio de Culturas. La producción, la circulación y el disfrute de la cultura tienen un lugar fundamental en la plataforma del candidato a Presidente del MAS-IPSP, cuyo primer paso es el restablecimiento del Ministerio.
translated: "Cultures are the lifeblood of our state plurinational" said Lucho Arce when it emerged that the transitional government Jeanine Áñez abolished the Ministry of Culture. Production, circulation and enjoyment of culture have a central place on the platform of the candidate for President of the MAS-IPSP, the first step is the restoration of the Ministry.

original: El Movimiento Al Socialismo (MAS), como el partido político más grande de Bolivia, tiene su propio sistema de conteo de votos que funcionará el día de las elecciones y permitirá conocer con precisión los resultados casi de manera inmediata al conteo de votos.
translated: Movement to Socialism (MAS), as the largest political party in Bolivia, has its own system of counting votes that will work on election day and let you know accurately the results almost immediately to the vote count.
